                        <text>Despite anything to the contrary in <changeable><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 22</citation></changeable> of the <changeable>Criminal Procedure (Reform and Modernisation) Act 2010</changeable>, the limitation period in respect of an offence against this Act or any regulations made under it ends on the date that is 10 years after the date on which the offence was committed.</text>
                      </para>
